cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SI

This paper presents a parallel algorithm for Group-Lasso (gLasso) that is scalable for large-scale datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm is based on a divide-and-conquer approach, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the theoretical guarantees of the algorithm, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the empirical results show that the algorithm can improve time efficiency without sacrificing accuracy, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
